name: NSFileProviderError
desc: A structure that contains information about File Provider errors.

items.name: var errorCode: Int
items.desc: A code that represents the error.

items.name: var code: Code
items.desc: A code that represents the error.

items.name: static var errorDomain: String
items.desc: A string that identifies the error domain.

items.name: var errorUserInfo: [String : Any]
items.desc: A dictionary that contains additional information about the error.

items.name: var userInfo: [String : Any]
items.desc: A dictionary that contains additional information about the error.

items.name: var localizedDescription: String
items.desc: A string that contains the localized description of the error.

items.name: enum NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: The error codes for the File Provider extension.

items.name: static var filenameCollision: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that an item with the same name already exists in the same directory.

items.name: static var insufficientQuota: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that the File Provider extension can’t upload the item because it would push the account over its quota.

items.name: static var noSuchItem: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that the specified item doesn’t exist.

items.name: static var notAuthenticated: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that you can’t verify the user’s credentials.

items.name: static var pageExpired: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that the page is too old, and that the system must restart the enumeration operation from the beginning.

items.name: static var serverUnreachable: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that the File Provider extension can’t reach the remote server.

items.name: static var syncAnchorExpired: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that the sync anchor is too old, and that the system must restart the sync operation from the beginning.

items.name: static var directoryNotEmpty: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating an attempt to nonrecursively delete a directory that isn’t empty.

items.name: static var providerNotFound: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that the File Provider manager can’t find the specified provider.

items.name: static var providerTranslocated: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating the File Provider extension is in a disabled state due to Gatekeeper’s restrictions for apps from outside the App Store.

items.name: static var olderExtensionVersionRunning: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that the registered provider in the system is an older version than the one the app uses.

items.name: static var newerExtensionVersionFound: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that the registered provider in the system is a newer version than the one the app uses.

items.name: static var nonEvictable: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that the File Provider extension can’t evict an item.

items.name: static var nonEvictableChildren: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that the File Provider extension can’t evict a directory because it contains nonevictable items.

items.name: static var unsyncedEdits: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating that the item contains unsynced changes.

items.name: static var cannotSynchronize: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating a failed sync attempt.

items.name: static var deletionRejected: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error indicating a failed deletion action.

items.name: static var versionNoLongerAvailable: NSFileProviderError.Code
items.desc: An error that indicates whether the specified version is no longer available.

items.name: static func == (NSFileProviderError, NSFileProviderError) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether two error values are equal.

items.name: static func != (NSFileProviderError, NSFileProviderError) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether two values are unequal.

items.name: func hash(into: inout Hasher)
items.desc: Hashes the essential components of a value by feeding them to the specified hasher.

items.name: var hashValue: Int
items.desc: The hash value for the instance.

items.name: init(Code, userInfo: [String : Any])
items.desc: Returns an error object with the specified error code and user info dictionary.
